{"questionId":"14069","questionHtml":"<p>Line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\"> <mi>L</mi> </math></span> passes through the origin and has a gradient of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\,\\theta \"> <mrow> <mtext>tan</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span>. Find the equation of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\"> <mi>L</mi> </math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct substitution of either gradient <strong>or</strong> origin into equation of line&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(do not accept <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = mx + b\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>b</mi> </math></span>)</p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\\,{\\text{tan}}\\,\\theta \"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>tan</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span>,&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y - 0 = m\\left( {x - 0} \\right)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>,&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = mx\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mi>x</mi> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y =&nbsp; - \\frac{3}{4}x\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mn>3</mn> <mn>4</mn> </mfrac> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2 N4</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L =&nbsp; - \\frac{3}{4}x\"> <mi>L</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mn>3</mn> <mn>4</mn> </mfrac> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14069","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.S_9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Line L passes through the origin and has a gradient of tan θ . Find the equation of L .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.1—Concepts, reliability and sampling techniques","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.8—Unit circle, Pythag identity, solving trig equations graphically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}